  <Method>
    <Step image="">Rub skirt steak with 1 tbsp sesame oil.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_164004.jpg">Sprinkle steak liberally with steak seasoning and MSG.</Step>
    <Step image="">Roll steak up and refrigerate for 2-4 hours.</Step>
    <Step image="">Remove steak from refrigerator, unroll and allow to come to room temperature. Meanwhile ...</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_164344.jpg">In a skillet, sweat the shallots in a little olive oil.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_164606.jpg">Add brown sauce, garlic, and half of the rosemary.Simmer for 10-20 minutes, until slightly reduced, skimming any foam.</Step>
    <Step image="">Strain the sauce, return to heat to keep warm.</Step>
    <Step image="">Preheat grill to high heat.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_171754.jpg">Oil the grill and add the steak.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_172508.jpg">Grill the steak to medium rare.</Step>
    <Step image="">Remove steak and allow to rest in a warmed oven. Meanwhile ...</Step>
    <Step image="">Bring a large pot of water to a boil.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add salt and pasta to boiling water, stir and cook to al dente.</Step>
    <Step image="">Drain the pasta, reserving some of the pasta water.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_174948.jpg">Return paste to pot. Combine with the spinach, sauce, 3/4 of the parsley and the remaining rosemary.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_175224.jpg">Cut the steak, across the grain, into strips.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_175525.jpg">Add any juices from the steak to the pot with the pasta.</Step>
    <Step image="Skirt%20Steak%20Farfalle_20250603_175808.jpg">Plate a serving of pasta. Top with a serving of steak. Garnish with the grated cheese and some parsley.</Step>
  </Method>
